


       
      What is sorrow's hue? Is it a somber shade of grey? A dreary color caught halfway  Between the worlds of black and white? Is it the deep and lonely blue Of the silent, tranquil sea? Is it the rich crimson Of blood spilt without reason? Is it subdued and pastel Or bold and strong? Is it the cloudy mist Of a single tear? If only I might know I would paint my soul.  This reminds me, check out  urlLink "A Dream Deferred"  by Langston Hughes. 
     

    
